Vroon began writing for the American Record Guide in 1983.
He became its chief editor and co-owner in 1987, moving its headquarters to Cincinnati.

In July 2014 Rowman & Littlefield published a book entitled Classical Music in a Changing Culture: Essays from the American Record Guide, a collection of essays from his "Critical Convictions" column in the magazine.

He worked as a Methodist minister from 1964 to 1972 and as a part-time instructor of Christian ethics at the University of Buffalo from 1982 to 1985.
